143
00:06:05,451 --> 00:06:09,757
the brilliant and loving people I've called friends for seven years.

144
00:06:09,757 --> 00:06:11,479
I'm still.

145
00:06:11,479 --> 00:06:16,806
Usually I'm an explorer, I'm thirsty for the new, new places, people, projects, and perspectives,

146
00:06:16,806 --> 00:06:20,631
but as a side effect, I have a hard time appreciating the present.

147
00:06:21,571 --> 00:06:24,451
But in this champagne moment, I'm glad I'm doing just that.

148
00:06:24,451 --> 00:06:26,232
New is good, but new is shallow.

149
00:06:26,232 --> 00:06:30,353
Along this poolside, I'm surrounded by people I love, trust, and lean on.

150
00:06:30,353 --> 00:06:34,773
It takes time to wade into the deep end of person.

151
00:06:34,773 --> 00:06:35,053
Wink.

152
00:06:35,053 --> 00:06:38,934
That was a sex joke.

153
00:06:38,934 --> 00:06:42,315
Two years ago at GDC, I rejected the term work-life balance.

154
00:06:42,315 --> 00:06:42,675
Still do.

155
00:06:42,675 --> 00:06:45,775
Work and non-work life can both be restful,

156
00:06:45,775 --> 00:06:48,756
but I think that what we mean by this is that we need variety.

157
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:52,061
Making things and consuming action and inaction

158
00:06:52,061 --> 00:06:56,843
Like your life your games need this balance of depth and variety for hyper light

159
00:06:56,843 --> 00:07:02,205
We spent the first half of production on depth the core combat dashing slashing guns

160
00:07:02,205 --> 00:07:06,687
We wanted to nail that before building the drifters world

161
00:07:06,687 --> 00:07:09,968
But while the depth of hyper lights core mechanics is crucial

162
00:07:09,968 --> 00:07:16,130
That's not the heart of the game and I've come to distrust the term core mechanics. We're gonna talk about it

163
00:07:17,847 --> 00:07:22,514
This term has its uses. In building a game, it's important to understand your primary interactions.

164
00:07:22,514 --> 00:07:25,438
Your core mechanics are the ones around which your variety will be based.

165
00:07:25,438 --> 00:07:27,641
They're the source of depth.

166
00:07:27,641 --> 00:07:30,084
But, in practice, I find it misleading.

167
00:07:30,084 --> 00:07:33,729
Core mechanic implies that it's the core of your whole game, and often it's not.

168
00:07:35,180 --> 00:07:38,381
We promised a preview of Hyper Light Drifter to our Kickstarter backers,

169
00:07:38,381 --> 00:07:41,843
and one year after the campaign, we were preparing to deliver that demo,

170
00:07:41,843 --> 00:07:45,405
but as we approached our release date for the preview, we realized...

171
00:07:45,405 --> 00:07:47,466
we had deep core mechanics, but a shallow core.

172
00:07:47,466 --> 00:07:49,987
We looked at our Kickstarter video, and then the demo we'd made,

173
00:07:49,987 --> 00:07:52,889
and we didn't see the connection.

174
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:55,190
Yes, our core mechanics are combat, but looking at that video,

175
00:07:55,190 --> 00:07:57,771
you see the true core of our game is the world.

176
00:07:57,771 --> 00:08:01,313
The feeling of being that drifter, the empty spaces, haunting tones,

177
00:08:01,313 --> 00:08:02,914
and ruined, forgotten depths.

178
00:08:02,914 --> 00:08:04,775
So we delayed the preview a week.

179
00:08:05,215 --> 00:08:09,716
put our heads back down, and developed the variety of moments that would enrich our world

180
00:08:09,716 --> 00:08:11,736
and form our real core.

181
00:08:11,736 --> 00:08:15,457
Alex spent time on environmental set pieces to enrich the world to give it the history

182
00:08:15,457 --> 00:08:18,578
it begged for, to suggest a purpose to all that killing and dashing.

183
00:08:18,578 --> 00:08:23,720
And don't get me wrong, we designed the Drifter's combat with the character and the message

184
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:24,040
in mind.

185
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:24,640
Powerful.

186
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:25,620
Fragile.

187
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:26,020
Medicated.

188
00:08:27,041 --> 00:08:31,323
Core mechanics are important and should serve your larger theme, but don't confuse them

189
00:08:31,323 --> 00:08:33,244
for the true core of your experience.

190
00:08:33,244 --> 00:08:37,386
They are the bedrock, the foundation on which you build the game, but people stand on a

191
00:08:37,386 --> 00:08:40,968
foundation and look up at the flying buttresses.

192
00:08:40,968 --> 00:08:44,009
Only you will know the work you put into making that floor sturdy and level.

193
00:08:44,009 --> 00:08:46,230
They'll remember the buttresses.

194
00:08:46,230 --> 00:08:49,172
I'll remember this.

195
00:08:49,172 --> 00:08:49,632
Poolside.

196
00:08:49,632 --> 00:08:50,452
Champagne.

197
00:08:50,452 --> 00:08:51,113
Friends.

198
00:08:51,113 --> 00:08:53,394
